  "summary": "Kaneko is shocked when Mukai mentions Mizuho, a topic not previously discussed. Sugata (Muto) reveals his motive for the visit, explaining that he intended to claim Mizuho but was prevented by her mother's death. He discloses that Mizuho's mother was Maria Kuchera, a foreigner he met in America. This revelation suggests that Mizuho is of mixed race, which would have caused intense opposition from the xenophobic Kagura family and the Kishijiro bloodline.\n\nSugata expresses his inability to protect Mizuho himself due to family opposition and asks Shizu to take on the responsibility. Although Shizu suggests Tsukimi might be a better choice, he reluctantly agrees to protect her while he travels to investigate the case. After Kaneko leaves, the group discusses the assignment. Mutsuji plays \"Death and the Maiden\" on an amplifier while performing string tricks. The conversation shifts to the nature of the investigation and the identity of the killer.\n\nThe group speculates on the motives of Kaname, suggesting he may have been torn between his inheritance and his mistress. Mukutsumi proposes a theory that the killer could be the mistress, implying that if she discovered Kaname's true intentions, the situation could turn deadly. The passage concludes as Hina announces dinner time and the narrator notes that Kumozawa is missing at 10:00 AM.",
